<body>
  <main class="container">
    <h1>Child Safety Standards</h1>
    <p class="updated">Last updated: April 25, 2026</p>

    <div class="alert">
      <strong>Zero Tolerance Policy:</strong> ClickChat (קליקצ'אט) has zero tolerance
      for Child Sexual Abuse and Exploitation (CSAE) and Child Sexual Abuse
      Material (CSAM). Any violation results in immediate account termination
      and reporting to the appropriate authorities.
    </div>

    <h2>1. Our Commitment</h2>
    <p>
      ClickChat is committed to providing a safe environment for all users and
      preventing the exploitation of minors. We comply with all applicable child
      safety laws, including the United States Code 18 U.S.C. § 2258A, and we
      cooperate with global law enforcement efforts to combat CSAE and CSAM.
    </p>

    <h2>2. Age Requirement</h2>
    <p>
      ClickChat is intended for users aged <strong>18 and older</strong>.
      Users must confirm they are at least 18 years old to register and use
      the service. Accounts identified as belonging to minors are immediately
      suspended and removed from the platform.
    </p>

    <h2>3. Prohibited Content and Behavior</h2>
    <p>The following are strictly prohibited on ClickChat:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Any sexual content involving or depicting minors (CSAM)</li>
      <li>Grooming, solicitation, or sexual exploitation of minors</li>
      <li>Sextortion or coercion targeting minors</li>
      <li>Sharing, requesting, or producing CSAM in any form</li>
      <li>Trafficking or facilitating the trafficking of minors</li>
      <li>Any communication intended to harm, abuse, or exploit a child</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>4. How We Prevent and Detect CSAE/CSAM</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>In-app reporting:</strong> Every user can report inappropriate
        behavior or content directly through the in-app report button.</li>
      <li><strong>Content moderation:</strong> We employ automated detection
        systems combined with human review to identify violations.</li>
      <li><strong>Account enforcement:</strong> Violating accounts are
        permanently banned, and the associated device/identifiers are blocked
        where technically possible.</li>
      <li><strong>Evidence preservation:</strong> When a violation is detected,
        relevant data is preserved for law enforcement.</li>
      <li><strong>Cooperation with authorities:</strong> We cooperate with
        NCMEC, INHOPE, and local law enforcement.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>5. Reporting CSAE/CSAM</h2>
    <h3>In-App Reporting</h3>
    <p>
      Users can report any chat or user violating our Child Safety Standards
      via the report button available in every conversation. Reports are
      reviewed promptly, typically within 24 hours.
    </p>

    <h3>External Reporting</h3>
    <p>
      To report CSAE/CSAM directly to ClickChat, contact us at the email
      below. To report directly to authorities:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>NCMEC CyberTipline (US/Global):</strong>
        <a href="https://report.cybertip.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">report.cybertip.org</a></li>
      <li><strong>INHOPE (international hotlines):</strong>
        <a href="https://www.inhope.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">inhope.org</a></li>
      <li><strong>Israel - 105 Hotline:</strong>
        <a href="https://www.gov.il/he/departments/general/safety_internet" target="_blank" rel="noopener">National Online Protection Center</a></li>
    </ul>

    <h2>6. Legal Compliance</h2>
    <p>
      ClickChat complies with all applicable child safety laws in the
      jurisdictions in which we operate. Suspected CSAM is reported to the
      National Center for Missing &amp; Exploited Children (NCMEC) and to
      regional and national authorities as required by law.
    </p>

    <h2>7. Contact - Child Safety Officer</h2>
    <div class="contact-box">
      <p><strong>Designated Child Safety Contact:</strong></p>
      <p>Email: <a href="mailto:appclickchat@gmail.com">appclickchat@gmail.com</a></p>
      <p>
        This contact is available to discuss our compliance with Child Safety
        Standards and our procedures for handling CSAM. We respond to all
        inquiries within 72 hours.
      </p>
    </div>

    <h2>8. Updates to These Standards</h2>
    <p>
      These Child Safety Standards may be updated periodically to reflect
      improvements in our practices or changes in legal requirements. The
      "Last updated" date at the top of this page indicates when these
      standards were last revised.
    </p>

